        "execSummary":  "The six-continent AI factory expansion signals that enterprise AI infrastructure is moving from concentrated hyperscaler data centers to a globally distributed compute fabric ΓÇö a shift with significant implications for data residency, latency, and sovereign AI compliance. For multinational enterprise leaders, the availability of NVIDIA-powered AI compute in more regions removes a key barrier to deploying AI workloads subject to data localization requirements. The entry of specialized cloud providers like CoreWeave and Nebius also introduces new procurement options that may offer better price-performance than hyperscaler defaults for GPU-intensive workloads. Organizations with global operations should revisit their AI infrastructure sourcing strategy in light of this expanded regional availability.",
