        "summary":  "Burley Kawasaki traces the evolution of enterprise software from traditional coding through low-code and no-code platforms, positioning AI as the next acceleration wave that enables business users to describe processes conversationally rather than learning platform-specific languages. The piece argues that AI fundamentally shifts the interaction model for enterprise software, democratizing innovation while requiring new governance structures.",
