        "summary":  "A Gartner survey of 469 executives found that 80% of CEOs expect AI automation to drive significant operational transformation as businesses shift toward autonomous systems. The deployment of AI agents will require executives to rethink profit models, workforce strategies, and revenue approaches, while enabling human employees to focus on specialized, intrinsic-value work rather than routine tasks.",
        "execSummary":  "AI agents are not a productivity tool layered on existing operations ΓÇö they are an architectural forcing function requiring enterprises to redesign how work flows, how value is measured, and how people are deployed. With 80% of CEOs expecting significant operational transformation, this is no longer a technology story but a business model story. Enterprise leaders who treat agent deployment as an IT project rather than a strategic restructuring will underperform peers who redesign their operating models first. This Gartner finding should anchor board-level conversations about AI investment priorities in the second half of 2026.",
