        "source":  "CIO Dive",
        "url":  "https://www.ciodive.com/news/agents-change-cybersecurity-frameworks/821801/",
        "date":  "2026-06-03",
        "theme":  "Orchestration",
        "summary":  "AI agents are reshaping enterprise cybersecurity by creating new risk profiles as they gain autonomy across business operations. Organizations face challenges managing agent permissions and oversight, with responsibility for security shifting from isolated IT teams to shared accountability across departments. Security experts emphasize the need for balanced governance frameworks that constrain agent capabilities while supporting business productivity.",
        "execSummary":  "As AI agents gain the ability to act autonomously across systems ΓÇö sending emails, executing transactions, accessing data ΓÇö they introduce attack surfaces that traditional cybersecurity frameworks were not designed to handle. The shift from isolated IT security to cross-departmental shared accountability is a structural change that will require new roles, new policies, and new vendor contracts. For enterprise leaders deploying agents in customer-facing or regulated environments, security architecture must be designed before, not after, agent rollout. Organizations that treat agent security as a post-deployment concern will face incidents that could have been designed out.",
        "vendorLean":  "Neutral",
        "imageUrl":  "https://imgproxy.divecdn.com/PJMqabQIdCexuv4O_yBDbMIRORxXC1rGJGN01mkOmug/g:ce/rs:fill:1200:675:1/Z3M6Ly9kaXZlc2l0ZS1zdG9yYWdlL2RpdmVpbWFnZS9HZXR0eUltYWdlcy0yMTg3ODQxMjQ4LmpwZw==.webp"
