        "date":  "2026-04-08",
        "theme":  "Strategy",
        "summary":  "An Altimetrik and HFS Research survey of over 500 technology leaders found that only 14% of enterprises deploying AI have a clearly defined strategy with established goals, while 71% operate with incomplete or developing plans. Tech leaders feel pressured to implement AI systems before establishing proper governance structures, accountability frameworks, or employee training programs, with companies prioritizing cost reduction over strategic problem-solving missing genuine ROI opportunities.",
        "execSummary":  "The enterprise AI race is producing a dangerous pattern: organizations are deploying AI at scale without the strategy, governance, or accountability frameworks needed to realize sustainable returns. With only 14% of AI-deploying enterprises operating from a clear strategy, the majority risk expensive course corrections when early investments fail to produce measurable value. For senior leaders, this research is a mandate to pause, define success criteria, and build governance before expanding AI deployment ΓÇö not after. The data also reveals that cost-reduction as the primary AI goal is a trap; organizations targeting strategic problem-solving consistently outperform on ROI.",
        "vendorLean":  "Neutral",
        "imageUrl":  "https://imgproxy.divecdn.com/H9qMLFosOvKrx_ijFYLbtvZO0E34K0pu2kiyiSuSkGg/g:ce/rs:fill:1200:675:1/Z3M6Ly9kaXZlc2l0ZS1zdG9yYWdlL2RpdmVpbWFnZS9HZXR0eUltYWdlcy0yMTYzOTU4NzQ2LmpwZw==.webp"
