        "source":  "CIO Dive",
        "url":  "https://www.ciodive.com/news/operating-models-modernize-companies-ai-success/823440/",
        "date":  "2026-06-22",
        "theme":  "Enterprise",
        "summary":  "A Publicis Sapient survey of 1,550 enterprise technology decision-makers reveals that while over 70% of U.S. respondents expect significant AI scaling within one to two years, only 20% believe their organizations are equipped to handle it. Legacy systems, fragmented data, siloed teams, and governance structures that slow decision-making represent the primary obstacles to realizing AI\u0027s business value.",
        "execSummary":  "Enterprise AI ambition is running far ahead of organizational readiness: 70% of companies expect to scale AI within two years, but only 20% believe their infrastructure can support it. The blockers are not model quality or compute costs ΓÇö they are legacy architecture, data fragmentation, and slow governance. For customer-support and operations leaders, this finding means that AI transformation programs must include legacy modernization as a prerequisite, not an afterthought. The gap between ambition and readiness is a strategic risk that will compound unless addressed in the 2026-2027 planning cycle.",
