        "theme":  "Agents",
        "summary":  "Organizations face a critical gap between their AI ambitions and execution capabilities, with 85% wanting to be agentic within three years but 76% reporting their current infrastructure cannot support that shift. The article argues that enterprises must redesign operations holistically around AI agents across three pillars ΓÇö technology stack, workforce dynamics, and success metrics ΓÇö rather than layering agents onto existing structures.",
        "execSummary":  "Agentic AI adoption will fail if enterprises treat it as a software deployment rather than an organizational redesign. The three-pillar framework ΓÇö technology, workforce, metrics ΓÇö provides a practical blueprint for leaders who recognize that agent success requires rethinking how work is structured, measured, and rewarded. The key implication for enterprise leaders: the organizations winning with agents in 2026 are those that changed their operating model first and deployed technology second. The 85%/76% ambition-vs-readiness gap is the defining strategic risk in enterprise AI today.",
