        "title":  "Learning to lead in a hybrid human-AI enterprise",
        "source":  "MIT Technology Review",
        "url":  "https://www.technologyreview.com/2026/06/09/1137830/learning-to-lead-in-a-hybrid-human-ai-enterprise/",
        "date":  "2026-06-09",
        "theme":  "Enterprise",
        "summary":  "As AI agent adoption accelerates, organizations must redesign employee roles, reskill workers toward higher-value tasks, and adapt workplace culture to manage blended human-AI teams. Leadership teams face the challenge of maintaining employee wellbeing and trust through robust governance and updated management practices as AI agents take on increasing shares of routine work.",
        "execSummary":  "Managing a workforce that includes both human employees and AI agents demands a new leadership discipline: one that balances productivity optimization with employee trust, wellbeing, and continuous reskilling. Organizations that treat workforce redesign as a technical staffing exercise rather than a cultural and leadership challenge risk employee disengagement and attrition at the moment they most need human judgment. For customer-support leaders, this signals that team manager roles must evolve to include AI agent supervision as a core competency alongside traditional people management skills.",
